cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use memory-blackbox in your research, please cite it as below."
title: "memory-blackbox: provenance and incident-reconstruction for AI agent memory"
abstract: >-
  memory-blackbox is a digital-forensics and incident-response toolkit for AI
  agent memory. It captures every memory read and write with cryptographically
  signed, tamper-evident provenance in an append-only ledger and provenance DAG,
  and reconstructs incidents by tracing actions to their originating memory and
  source, computing blast radius, detecting belief drift, verifying integrity,
  and producing rollback plans.
type: software
authors:
